Lieutenant-Colonel Thandi Mbombo said security at the Eland Mine Shaft recovered 11 bodies on Monday and alerted police to it. She said police recovered 13 more bodies on Tuesday bringing the total number to 24 bodies."We can't confirm whether they are illegal miners or not. Some of them had name tags on but the management of the mine said they didn't work for the mine " Mbombo said.She said the mine reported an explosion last week on Thursday and that police would investigate the cause of the explosion.Harmony Gold spokesperson Marian van der Walt confirmed that security recovered 11 bodies on Monday and handed the matter over to the police and the department of mineral resources.Van der Walt said the Elands Mine Shaft wasn't operational anymore.-TMG Digital/TimesLIVE